.TH AUTOSCROLL\-X11 1 "April 2026" "0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
autoscroll\-x11 \- Windows\-like middle\-click autoscroll for X11
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B autoscroll\-x11
[\fIOPTION\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B autoscroll\-x11
monitors the middle mouse button and activates smooth autoscroll when the
button is held beyond a configurable threshold.  Releasing the button
immediately cancels scrolling so that normal middle\-click behaviour is
preserved for short presses.
.PP
An anchor overlay is displayed at the pointer position when autoscroll
becomes active.  Moving the pointer away from the anchor in any direction
scrolls in that direction at a speed proportional to the distance.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-tray
Start with only a system\-tray icon; do not open the main window.
.TP
.B \-\-debug
Enable verbose debug logging to standard error.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the version string and exit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B DISPLAY
X11 display to connect to (required).
.TP
.B AUTOSCROLL_DEBUG
Set to any non\-empty value to enable debug logging.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/xdg/autostart/autoscroll\-x11.desktop
XDG autostart entry.
.TP
.I /usr/lib/autoscroll\-x11/autoscroll_x11/
Python package installed by the Debian package.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR xdotool (1),
.BR xinput (1)
